LPS LAPTOP PICKUP TODAY AND TOMORROW!

Lynn Public Schools has made laptops available for ALL STUDENTS in Grades 3-12 for the 2020-21 school year. If you have a child(ren) in these grades and HAVE NOT picked up a laptop, we urge you to do so.

LPS is encouraging all students to use these devices rather than personal devices for remote learning due to their setup and features.

You may pick up a device:

Wednesday September 2nd at the LVTI Annex from 8:30 AM until 2 PM at 90 Commercial Street
or
Thursday September 3rd at English High School at 50 Goodridge Street, Lynn, MA

PLEASE HAVE YOUR STUDENT ID AS WELL AS A PEN WITH YOU. If you do not have your student ID, please call your school.

Grades Kindergarten, Grade 1 and Grade 2: The city is working hard to get devices for all LPS students in a timely manner.

Unfortunately, they may not be ready for pickup by the start of school.

NEW â€“ Influenza Requirement - Visit our Health Services website for details and requirements for all grades.

http://www.lynnschools.org/departments/healthservices.shtml?gpm=1_8

NEW â€“ Influenza Requirement
1 dose; seasonal influenza vaccine for the current flu season (July-June) must be received annually for anyone 6 months of age or older by December 31st. New students entering between January 1st and March 31st must have received a dose of vaccine for the current flu season for entry. Depending on the childâ€™s flu vaccination history, ACIP may recommend a second dose of flu vaccine in the same season. In these cases, the second dose is recommended but is not required for entry.

post_text:
Reopen Survey - We need your input/feedback!
https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/lpsparentsurvey2

Our goal is to ensure that all students have high-quality learning experiences and that families have everything they need. During this difficult time, we want to ensure that we are responsive to the most critical needs of our families and soliciting input for our plans going forward. It is very important to hear from LPS families about which supports should continue and those that should be improved or added.

This survey is an important opportunity to help us understand your experiences and needs during this time and will help with our planning. Thank you in advance for taking the time to respond. Note that you are welcome to skip any question you do not want to answer.

This survey will be available until June 22nd.

https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/lpsparentsurvey2

Free Citizenship Services for Permanent Residents
Although we are in lockdown, NAAM is still here to help you apply for US citizenship. Our citizenship classes are now available online, and NAAM representatives can help you with your citizenship application over the phone. Application assistance and classes are free of charge.
www.naamass.org

Civics & History Classes for the Naturalization Interview
Classes are now being held online via ZOOM. Call us at 781-593-0100x14 to register for classes.

For assistance pleas call us at 781-593-0100x17 to find out if you are eligible to apply for US citizenship. We will help you complete your citizenship application and submit it to the US
Citizenship Immigration Services Office. Call today to register and receive help with your application. 330 Lynnway, Suite 302, Lynn, MA 01901 Questions? Contact citizenshipNAAM@gmail.com.

post_text:
Hello everyone!

I wanted to let you know about a special Earth Day event happening online tonight 4/22 at 6:30. Storyteller Diane Edgecomb will be sharing her Earth Day stories on Vimeo. Her stories are always fun, captivating and educational for all!

Copy and paste this link into your web browser to join:
https://vimeo.com/408199975

Tales for the Earth with Diane Edgecomb
â€œTales for the Earthâ€ is a celebration of Nature and all the simple things we can do to help. This beloved performance is both educational and entertaining,â€¦
vimeo.com

Here is a description of her performance:
â€œTales for the Earthâ€ is a celebration of Nature and all the simple things we can do to help. This beloved performance is both educational and entertaining, exploring topics such as water conservation, recycling and the wonder of the creatures all around us through involving and participatory narratives. What shines through the entire presentation is a love and respect for our place in nature; with many ideas communicated about how we can create a difference.

I hope you can join us!

post_text:
What to do with your Kindergarten student? Try one (or all) of these websites: Kindergarten Websites

www.starfall.com Review letters of the alphabet especially the vowels a, e, i, o, u
https://www.storylineonline.net/ listen to a story with your child and ask questions about the story. Use the hamburger to draw or write the beginning, middle and end of the story.
www.jmathpage.com Math games available. Kindergarten will be working on naming and describing plane shapes: circle, square, triangle, rectangle, hexagon.
https://www.ixl.com/math/kindergarten Practice addition, subtraction, and numbers up to 20.
https://www.readinga-z.com/books/leveled-books/
Read books at the aa, A, B, C levels with your child.
https://www.gonoodle.com/blog/gonoodle-games-movement-app-for-kids/ Movement and exercise games for children
https://pbskids.org/curiousgeorge/busyday/ Variety of science and math games for young children
http://peepandthebigwideworld.com/en/ Variety of science and math games for your children
